body: 71 (return) [ The secret intentions of Julian are revealed by the late bishop of Gloucester, the learned and dogmatic Warburton; who, with the authority of a theologian, prescribes the motives and conduct of the Supreme Being. The discourse entitled _Julian_ (2d edition, London, 1751) is strongly marked with all the peculiarities which are imputed to the Warburtonian school.]
